Utterance.UttText: The bed 1, Luke Geller, 74 yrs old under Dr Li, came in with Alzheimer's dse.
His obs are all stable, he is very confused and can be very aggressive and he needs 2-3 persons for transfer using a sling lifter.
He is doubly incontinent of urine and faeces and He's got a pad insitu.
He needs to be fed and to sit upright when eating.
He needs to have his tablets crushed and needs to have referral to speech pathology.
He needs PAC (pressure area care) and pressure relieving mattress because he stays in bed most of the times.
